    "media_ideology": "Right",
    "relative_ideology": "Right",
    "absolute_ideology": "Right",
    "news": [
        {
            "id": 0,
            "text": "Policy 'openly discriminates against white teachers based only on the color of their skin,' lawyer says"
        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "text": "Minnesota Public Schools reached an agreement with its teachers' union to institute a policy that will discriminate against white teachers during layoffs, according to a report from Alpha News."
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "text": "The agreement, which the union reached in March following a two-week strike, upends the seniority-based layoff system under which teachers who have been employed the least amount of time are the first to be fired."
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "text": "Under the new rules, if a minority teacher is set to be laid off, the district will instead fire the next least senior teacher who is white."
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "text": "\"If [laying off] a teacher who is a member of a population underrepresented among licensed teachers in the site, the district shall excess the next least senior teacher, who is not a member of an underrepresented population,\" reads the agreement, which goes into effect next spring."
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "text": "The justification for the racial discrimination is to \"remedy the continuing effects of past discrimination,\" according to the school district."
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "text": "Minnesota Public Schools' policy is the latest example of teachers' efforts to institute policies favoring minority teachers in hiring and compensation in order to achieve racial equity."
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "text": "Staff at New York City's elite Dalton School in 2020 demanded the administration pay off black faculty's student debt, the Washington Free Beacon reported."
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "text": "The Minnesota policy also favors minorities when the district reinstates teachers."
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "text": "\"The District shall deprioritize the more senior teacher, who is not a member of an underrepresented population, in order to recall a teacher who is a member of a population underrepresented among licensed teachers,\" the agreement reads."
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "text": "James Dickey, senior trial counsel at the Upper Midwest Law Center, told Alpha News the policy is racially discriminatory and unconstitutional."
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "text": "\"The [collective bargaining agreement] \u2026 openly discriminates against white teachers based only on the color of their skin, and not their seniority or merit,\" Dickey said."
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "text": "\"Minneapolis teachers and taxpayers who oppose government-sponsored racism like this should stand up against it.\""
        }
    ],
